args: That looks to be the last of them, Ranzal.\nWe should return to the castle—I tire.
No surprise with how much butt-kickin' ya\ndid. That power of yers is the real deal!
Gotta admit though, it's kinda surprisin'\nto see a kid like you takin' down a whole\nmess'a crazy fiends.
Our power was designed to seal away\nthe Other. So fiends? A simple matter.
And I am no ＂kid,＂ as I have stated.
Ah, crap! Sorry. It's just that babyface'a\nyers what makes me forget, yeah?
Say, is yer little bro the same?\nDoes he look six or whatever?
Shion? No. My brother possesses not my\nTutelary power, so his mana has been\nunaffected—thus his appearance as well.
Shion! What are you doing here?!
Looking for YOU, you idiot!\nWhere have you BEEN?!
You can't just wander off without a word\nand expect me not to come looking!\nNow come on—we're going back.
Look, the boss brought Delphi here,\nso we ain't just gonna let him walk\noff what if he don't wanna.
So what say we all head over to the\ncastle and figure this out, yeah?
...So you came because you were worried\nabout your brother's health? I see.

I didn't know Delphi paid such a price for
his power—but I suppose something that
pollutes a person's mana wouldn't be
great for their health.
That must be why he collapsed\nwhen we first met.

Likely so. Each time he uses his power,
the strain on his body is tremendous—
which is why I'm trying to get him to
come home with me and RELAX.
But if you're going to keep him here,\nthen I insist on staying with him.
I don't have a problem with that.\nBut what about you, Delphi?
Forget me, Shion. Leave this place.\nContinue your life apace.
Forget you?! No! I can't ever for—
I grow weary of you, boy!
Your presence is a burden.\nYour very appearance a misery.
This power? It was meant for you.\nYet now it lies heavy upon MY brow.
All because of the accident when our\nparents tried to pass it down to you.
I've a power which drains my life,\ntwo parents moldering in the grave,\nand a brother near to useless.
Delphi, you...you can't mean this!\nYou've always been so kind to—

Kind? No. My actions were no kindness.
Only a sort of pity for a boy too foolish
and inept to care for himself—a pity
that made me shoulder YOUR burden.
I've endured it these long years for the\nsake of our tribe. But the tribe? Gone.\nSo now my mind can be spoken freely.
Now go. Leave me. Never return.\nThe very sight of you sickens me.
Why are you doing this? Whyyy?!
I did not mean for you to see that,\nYour Highness.
This matter? Pray set it from your mind.\nIt is personal—nothing more.
Well, I suppose I've no right\nto judge another's family.
That aside, my preparations for the ritual\nnear their end at last.
There is but one final thing\nI must ask of you:
Our tribe's sacred mission?\nAssigned by your ancestors.\nCodified by their bloodline.
The ritual requires proof of consent.\nThe dragonblood serves as proof.
I need but a few drops at most.\nMay I ask it of you?
Well, your family HAS gone through\na lot to protect the seals...
And I don't think I'll miss a drop or two.\nSo yes, Delphi. That's fine.
Can I just say one thing, though?
I don't know what's going on between you\nand your brother, but I know nothing good\ncomes from familial strife.
You sound very like my brother\nin this moment, Highness.
